  "prompt": "Is it normal to have no dreams while sleeping?",
  "response": "Yes, it is quite normal for some people to feel like they don't have dreams while sleeping. However, it's important to note that everyone likely experiences dreaming during their sleep cycles, particularly during REM (rapid eye movement) sleep. The difference lies in whether or not you recall your dreams upon waking.\n\nMany factors can influence dream recall, including sleep quality, stress levels, and individual differences. If you are concerned about your dreaming patterns or lack thereof, consulting with a healthcare professional or sleep specialist may provide useful insights and guidance.",
